nodes.bodyText:
When --streaming=true is not specified, this happens:



      beam/runners/google-cloud-dataflow-java/src/main/java/org/apache/beam/runners/dataflow/DataflowRunner.java


        Lines 869 to 871
      in
      996c8d2







           if (containsUnboundedPCollection(pipeline)) { 




             options.setStreaming(true); 




           } 





So the unmodified ValidatesRunner test suite uses batch mode when possible and streaming when necessary. We expect essentially all users to use the unmodified form and let it "just work". But very few of our ValidatesRunner tests have unbounded PCollections so streaming is largely untested in this mode.
It may be overkill to change this title. I got worried it would be confused for a "batch only" mode, which it is not.

